The Kwara State House of Assembly has lauded President Muhammadu Buhari and the APC for shortlisting two ministerial nominees from the state. The house resolved to write the president to show their appreciation which followed Matter of General Public Importance raised by Member representing Ojomu/Balogun constituency, Prince Saheed Popoola, on the two ministerial slots allotted to the state. The Speaker, Engr. Yakubu Danladi Salihu, while reading the resolutions of the House, praised the president and the APC for appreciating the enormous contributions of the state to the success of the party at the just concluded general elections and enjoined nominees to translate this to meaningful development for the state.  Ministerial slots: Kwara assembly lauds Buhari, APC Groups disagree over Lai Mohammed’s nomination Troubled diplomacy: When states’ APC rejected ambassadorial nominees Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin